Titolo: Steve Davis Snooker

Anno: 1984

Descrizione: Steve Davis Snooker is a sports simulation video game developed by CDS Software, and published by CDS Software in 1985,. The budget release published by Blue Ribbon Software reached the top of the UK charts in May 1988. Steve Davis Snooker simulates the cue sport snooker. Released under licence from 6-time Snooker World Champion, Steve Davis.
The game is the first to feature a license of a professional snooker player, with later Jimmy White creating the Cueball series.  CDS called the game the "ultimate successor" to their 1983 pool simulator, titled Pool. Davis would also be involved with the 1989 follow-up Steve Davis World Snooker, as well as 1996's Virtual Snooker.